quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  72,14,"“ ‘Among us are some who submit their will, and some that stray from justice. Now those who submit their will, they have found the right path"
  72,15,"“But those who stray, they are fuel for hellfire.”"
  72,16,"If they had remained on the path, We should certainly have bestowed on them rain in abundance"
  72,17,"That We might try them. But if any turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will cause him to undergo a severe penalty"
  72,18,“And the places of worship are for God. So do not invoke any one along with God
  72,19,"“Yet when the devotee of God stands forth to invoke Him, they make around him a dense crowd.”"
  72,20,"Say, “I do no more than invoke my Lord, and I do not join any with Him.”"
  72,21,"Say, “It is not in my power to cause you harm, nor to bring you to right conduct.”"
  72,22,"Say, “No one can save me from God, nor would I find refuge except with Him"
  72,23,"“Unless I proclaim what I receive from God and His messages. For any who goes against God and His messenger, for them is hell. They will dwell therein forever.”"
  72,24,"Then, when they see that which they are promised, then will they know who it is that is weakest in support and least in numbers"
  72,25,"Say, “I do not know whether that which you are promised is near, nor whether my Lord will appoint for it a distant term"
  72,26,"“He knows the unknown, and He does not show anyone His unknown"
  72,27,"“Except a messenger whom He has chosen, and then He makes a group of watchers march before him and behind him"
  72,28,"“That He may know that they have brought and delivered the Messages of their Lord, and He surrounds all that are with them, and takes account of every single thing.”"